### Products
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/Products
 
###
 
### Customers
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/Customers
 
###
 
### Sales Orders
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/SalesOrders
 
###
 
### Suppliers
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/Suppliers
 
###
 
### Categories
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/Categories
 
###
 
### Filter Products
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/Products?$filter=price gt 100
 
###
 
### Order By Rating
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/Products?$orderby=rating desc
 
###
 
### Filter Customers
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/Customers?$filter=creditLimit gt 1000
 
###
 
### Expand Customer in Sales Orders
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/SalesOrders?$expand=customer
 
###
 
### Expand Supplier and Category in Products
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/Products?$expand=supplier,category
 
###
 
### Product Catalog Report
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/report/ProductCatalogReport
 
###
 
### Order Report
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/report/OrderReportView
 
###
 
### Low Stock Alert
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/report/LowStockAlertView
 
###
 
### Deep Insert Product
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/admin/Products
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
    "name": "Gaming Laptop",
    "description": "High Performance Laptop",
    "price": 1200,
    "currency_code": "USD",
    "stock": 20,
    "minStock": 5,
    "rating": 4.8
}


 
@sales = http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/sales
 
### Test 1: Create order without customer (should fail)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
  "orderDate": "2026-06-15",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_ID": "p1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 50.00
    }
  ]
}
 
### Test 2: Create order with past date (should fail)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
  "customer_ID": "c1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "orderDate": "2020-01-01",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_ID": "p1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 50.00
    }
  ]
}
 
### Test 3: Create order with invalid item (quantity 0)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
  "customer_ID": "c1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "orderDate": "2026-06-15",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_ID": "p1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "quantity": 0,
      "unitPrice": 50.00
    }
  ]
}
 
### Test 4: Create valid order (should succeed + auto-calculate totals!)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
  "customer_ID": "c1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "orderNumber": "SO-201",
  "orderDate": "2026-06-15",
  "currency_code": "USD",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_ID": "p1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 499.99
    },
    {
      "product_ID": "p1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111112",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 29.99
    }
  ]
}
 
### Test 5: Try invalid status transition (New → Delivered should fail)
PATCH {{sales}}/SalesOrders(f6f681f2-f6ab-4fb3-bb8e-6b3f3efbab96)
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
  "status": "Delivered"
}
 
### Test 6: Valid status transition (New → Confirmed)
PATCH {{sales}}/SalesOrders(f6f681f2-f6ab-4fb3-bb8e-6b3f3efbab96)
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
  "status": "Confirmed"
}


###
### Call unbound action: GenerateReport
POST http://localhost:4004/analytics/GenerateReport
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
    "reportType": "Sales",
    "startDate": "2026-01-01",
    "endDate": "2026-05-31"
}


### Confirm a specific order
POST http://localhost:4004/sales/SalesOrders(859b6407-34be-4229-9c57-d8c96cd90c15)/SalesService.confirm
Content-Type: application/json
 
{}
 
### Cancel a specific order (with reason parameter)
POST http://localhost:4004/sales/SalesOrders(859b6407-34be-4229-9c57-d8c96cd90c15)/SalesService.cancel
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
    "reason": "Customer changed their mind"
}
 
### Ship an order (with tracking info)
POST http://localhost:4004/sales/SalesOrders(859b6407-34be-4229-9c57-d8c96cd90c15)/SalesService.ship
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
    "trackingNumber": "TRK-2026-ABC123",
    "carrier": "FedEx"
}
 
 